longBusinessSummary: Tinna Rubber and Infrastructure Limited manufactures value-added products from recycling waste and end of life tires in India and internationally. The company offers crumb, micronized, and coated rubber powders; high tensile reclaim rubbers; crumb rubber modifiers; crumb rubber and polymer modified bitumen; bitumen emulsions; and steel abrasives, as well as reclaimed rubber/ultrafine crumb rubber compounds, cut wire shots, and polymer composites, etc. Its products are used for making/repairing of roads; and rubber mates and tiles, tires, and conveyor belt applications. The company serves the tire and auto parts industries. The company was formerly known as Tinna Overseas Limited and changed its name to Tinna Rubber and Infrastructure Limited in December 2012. Tinna Rubber and Infrastructure Limited was founded in 1977 and is based in New Delhi, India.
